            {
                "title": "Severance for Employees",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "In Italy, there is no severance pay or redundancy compensation as such. However, upon the termination of the employment relationship, the employee receives the so-called TFR (Trattamento di Fine Rapporto), which is a part of workers' wages whose payment is deferred upon the termination of the employment relationship."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "Hence, it cannot be considered proper severance pay, since it is constituted by a certain amount of salary set aside each month."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "The TFR is calculated according to the formula of a year's overall salary divided by 13.5, plus 1.5% for each year of service plus compensation for inflation."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "The TFR must be paid to the worker in any case of termination of the employment relationship."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "Statutory time off": [
            {
                "title": "Paid Time Off",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "Full-time employees are entitled to 20 working days of paid time off (PTO) a year. PTO accrues monthly at 1.67 days per month. Employees are allowed to take at least 10 working days in a row."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "PTO for part-time employees will be calculated according to the weekly working hours."
                    }
